CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. B10 reads: "Chi Delta Mu Fraternity Entertains Lavishly" Portion of accompanying article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. A7 by Toki Schalk Johnson reads:"Wednesday brought forth the annual dinner dance given by the Chi Delta Mu Fraternity in beautifully decorated New Arena."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four men wearing tuxedos, and five women, including one front left wearing short sleeved satin gown with wide off the shoulder collar, seated at rectangular banquet table for Chi Delta Mu dinner dance in New Arena Supper Club
